    Jose E. Mata       E-Mail
    Jose E. Mata is originally from Houston, Texas and has resided in Montgomery County since 1990. He graduated from Sam Houston State University with his Bachelor in Business Administration in 1987. While working full-time, he received his Doctorate of Jurisprudence from South Texas College of Law in Houston on May 1995. Mr. Mata began in private practice April 1996 until June 1997. At that time, he went to work at the Montgomery County Attorneys Office as a prosecutor. He was employed there until he returned to private practice and opened the Law Office of Jose Mata in January 1999 in Conroe Texas. Although Mr. Mata practices primarily in Montgomery County, he has represented clients in many of the surrounding counties. As a former prosecutor, Mr. Mata primarily practices criminal defense law. However, he has represented various clients on personal injury cases, divorce and other civil matters. Not Certified By The Texas Board Of Legal Specialization.

    Southern Empress       E-Mail
    Travel back in time to a grand era of sumptuous hospitality and Victorian splendor as a guest aboard Southern Empress Cruises. The grandeur and charm of this authentic riverboat serves as an elegant setting for Sunday Brunch, a romantic evening of dinner and dancing, or a private party on special occasions such as a birthday, anniversary, wedding, and corporate banquet.

    As the Southern Empress cruises on Lake Conroe, guests can enjoy the romance and enchantment of dining and dancing. Lunch and dinner cruises are available. Menu items are selectable. Large parties may prefer our elegant hors d'voures served to 200 or more guests. DJ music service of the sixties, seventies, eighties and beyond. Two of the three spacious decks on the Southern Empress are enclosed and offer year-round cruising comfort.

    The opulence of the 1800's is evident throughout this elegant paddleboat with features reminiscent of the Victorian era. An antique-style cash bar, custom-cut leaded and beveled crystal doors and windows, chandeliers, polished brass, solid oak carved moldings, and raised paneling compliment the grand interior of this gracious Southern lady.

    Authentic embossed tin ceilings and a rich setting of colors and textures that include wine and violet velour, damask linens, delicate lace and floral carpets add to the ambiance and charm of the Southern Empress.
